do you understand how instant runoff voting works?

"The alternative vote (also known as instant-runoff voting) is a voting system where each voter can vote for as many of the options as they want, ranking them in order of their preference. At the end of each round of voting"

"the candidate with the least votes is eliminated, and every ballot that had that candidate as the top pick switches to their next-preferred not-yet-eliminated candidate. This has the effect of simulating what would have happened if the eliminated"
"hadn't run in the first place, which allows people to more easily vote based on their preferences, rather than what they think might realistically win."
So when something got "0" votes, that means no one had it at the TOP of their list
Could have been lower down - maybe even somewhat high up.  The system isn't perfect
